events.event_name: Record US Natural Gas Storage Withdrawal
events.description: US energy firms withdrew 360 billion cubic feet of natural gas from storage in the week ended January 30, 2026, marking the largest weekly drop on record.
An extreme cold weather event that increased demand for heating.

facts.fact_text: US energy firms withdrew 360 billion cubic feet of natural gas from storage in the week ended January 30, 2026.
